;THE TASKA-MALTODP3 NAMELY TASKA-T COMPLEXES WAS CRYSTALLIZED USING THE STREAK SEEDING METHOD WITH A COMMERCIALLY AVAILABLE SEEDING TOOL, HAMPTON RESEARCH, USA. THE SEEDING TOOL WAS DIPPED INTO A DROP CONTAINING TASKA-APO,PDB ID 5A2A, CRYSTALS AND STREAKED ON THE DROPS THAT CONSISTED OF 0.3 UL 6 MG/ML TASKA PROTEIN AND 0.3 UL RESERVOIR SOLUTION 0.1 M CALCIUM ACETATE, 0.1 M SODIUM CACODYLATE PH 6.5, AND 18 % W/V POLYETHYLENE GLYCOL 8,000 WITH 20 MM MALTOTRIOSE.
